</p>
<h3>Infrastructure Components</h3>
<p>
    The following components provide the infrastructure for the ELEFLEX<sup>&reg;</sup> platform. 
    The architecture utilizes bootstrapper to provide an entrypoint for startup tasks that are used to configure the system at startup.
    Structuremap is used for dependency injection and inversion of control (IOC) capabilities to promote loose coupling and good development practices.
    AutoMapper is used for object to object mapping between storage, domain and service layers.
    Common Logging is used to provide a generic logging mechanism for all components in the system.
</p>
